HEADWORD: Treadwheel
<hw>Tread"wheel`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A wheel turned by
persons or animals, by treading, climbing, or pushing with the feet,
upon its periphery or face. See <er>Treadmill</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Treague</ent>⟦br⟧
